Merge branch 'langtags'

* langtags:
  LanguageTags: some specs
Utils: performance fix for #parse_qvalues (thx for baton)
a bunch of new specs for LanguageTag
minor performance fix of LanguageTag#matches? (prevents duplicate calls of #recompose)
LanguageTag: further experimentation with "basic filtering" rules
optional support for canonical forms of grandfathered LanguageTags; fixes in validation
LanguageTag: further work with compose+recompose; minor fixes
Languages#extract_full_language_info removed due to uselessness (there's should be a LanguageTag wrapper)
second attempt to make MIMETypes faster (+10-17% on 1.9.1+, OK on 1.8.7-1.9.0); unnecessary stuff removed.
dirty attempt to increase performance in 1.9.1+
Languages: conformance to RFC5646, additional validations (variants), extlang and so on

Usability of Rack::Acceptable::MIMETypes
#qualify_mime_type, #weigh_mime_type should be able to accept MIMEType snippet (String) or a parsed media-range (Array) as a first argument
#detect_best_mime_type should be able to work with the set of MIME-Types (media-ranges, preliminary parsed; necessary for 'provides-only-something' middlewares).
the full list of grandfathered/grandfathered-and-irregular Language Tags
Languages#parse_locales should ignore 'i' and 'x' singletons (when they are primary)

* Utils has been splitted up. Now we have:
  - Rack::Acceptable::Utils (definitive stuff - splitters, simple parsers etc)
  - Rack::Acceptable::Encodings (Accept-Encoding parser and negotiation)
  - Rack::Acceptable::Charsets (Accept-Charset parsers and negotiation)
  - Rack::Acceptable::Languages (parsers of the Accept-Language header and Language-Tags)
  - Rack::Acceptable::MIMETypes (parsers, qualification and negotiation of the MIME-Types).

* fixed 'whitespace-insensitivity' issue
* added Utils#normalize_header (which is able to conveniently transform #(ele) lists; specially for perfectionists)
* more specs
support for Accept-Language header and Language Tags, some minor fixes.

* balance between RFC and convenience
* cleanup in Utils (regexps)
* more sensible examples in benchmarks

* fixes: accept-extension key/value pairs (values are OPTIONAL, acc. to pattern in RFC 2616, sec. 14.1)
* Utils#parse_media_range_and_qvalue: it extracts only necessary data, and faster than full parse of MIME-Type.
specs: valid examples with non-tokens in parameter/accept-params of the MIME-Type

* definitive parsers should be whitespace-insensitive (RFC 2616, sec. 2.1)
* definitive parsers should respect 1#(something) rule (RFC 2616, sections: 2.1, 14.1-14.4)
* cleanup in Const and Helpers, etc.
bench for negotiation: strong algorithm vs weak-but-quick
RDoc markup (well, docs should be readable =/), type fix in Utils#detect_acceptable_mime_type
performance; more examples in detect_best_encoding benchmark
little fix in the inner comments
fix: stable sorting instead of plain sort_by; because detection of the best MIME-Types (or another stuff) SHOULD respect order of items in request-header (when other things being equal)
Utils#detect_acceptable_mime_type (quick and rough version of detect_best_mime_type)
improved Utils#parse_http_accept_language; performance (no more ordering in definitive parsers) + associated specs
second portion of shared specs + cleanup

* block support for Utils#extract_qvalues
* Utils#parse_http_accept_language with proper validations; first portion of associated specs
* more specs
Utils#parse_media_range; changes in Utils#parse_mime_type; associated specs and docs
